Hundreds of recordings were done, often live at underground places, and distributed on an estimated 80+ semi-official cassettes. Later in his short career, he also appeared as a featured artist with orchestras. Arkady died from a cerebral hemorrhage and these days, hardly any copies of the 'original' tapes can be found. There is a vast amount of pseudo-rereleases and compilations of his recordings, though.
